l health of the organization&nbsp;</div><div>ïƒ˜ Preparing a budget for Board approval, and ensuring that the organization operates&nbsp;</div><div>within budgetary guidelines</div><div>ïƒ˜ Ensuring the organization maintains sound financial practices and has adequate funds&nbsp;</div><div>to carry out it work</div><div>6. Developing and overseeing the team that manages infrastructure, culture, people,&nbsp;</div><div>analytics and program implementation using the Coalition values and competency&nbsp;</div><div>matrix.&nbsp;</div><div>ïƒ˜ Building out Coalition infrastructure commensurate with program needs&nbsp;</div><div>ïƒ˜ Assuring training, development, engagement, and retention of staff&nbsp;</div><div>ïƒ˜ Internal succession planning&nbsp;</div><div>7. Overseeing and managing critical external interfaces&nbsp;</div><div>ïƒ˜ Assuring ongoing engagement of members and funding sources&nbsp;</div><div>ïƒ˜ Continuing to identify and engage potential partner organizations</div><div>ïƒ˜ Overseeing intentional and proactive outreach to legislators, researchers in the field,&nbsp;</div><div>and potential collaborators</div><div>ïƒ˜ Maintaining the Coalitionâ€™s visibility and desirability as a recipient of grants and&nbsp;</div><div>partnership opportunities&nbsp;</div><div>ïƒ˜ Actively engaging with local social and political leaders to be a full participant in&nbsp;</div><div>ïƒ˜ Camdenâ€™s socioeconomic and infrastructure development&nbsp;</div><div>ïƒ˜ Working closely with the Board to coordinate Board ambassadorship and support&nbsp;</div><div>Board development&nbsp;</div><div>ïƒ˜ Working closely with Board members and community partners to insure an inclusive&nbsp;</div><div>perspective&nbsp;</div><div>ïƒ˜ Assuring the broad universe of stakeholders that the Coalition appreciates its strength&nbsp;</div><div>to be dependent upon its partnerships with those organizations.</div></div><div><div>Appendix</div><div>Vision: A transformed healthcare system that ensures every individual recei ves</div><div>a whole-person care rooted in authentic healing relationships.</div><div>M ission: Spark a field and movement that unites communities of caregivers in&nbsp;</div><div>Camden and across the nation to improve the wellbeing of individuals with&nbsp;</div><div>complex health and social needs.</div><div>Core Values</div><div>Compassion and Respect</div><div>â€¢ Being kind &amp; respectful to everyone (even those who are difficult to be so to)</div><div>â€¢ Meeting people where they are at (even if they arenâ€™t ready/open to change)</div><div>â€¢ Open/accepting body language (Maintaining eye contact, handshaking, etc.)</div><div>â€¢ Assuming positive intent</div><div>â€¢ Displaying empathy &amp; active listening skills (reflection, pause, &amp; understanding)</div><div>â€¢ Treating everyone in a consistent manner (regardless of the situation)</div><div>â€¢ Being honest &amp; showing integrity</div><div>Innovation</div><div>â€¢ Not being afraid to take risk/present a new idea &amp; use feedback</div><div>â€¢ Planned, evaluated, &amp; purposeful iteration</div><div>â€¢ Embracing change</div><div>â€¢ Learning quickly from failure</div><div>Communication and Collaboration</div><div>â€¢ Trusting other people on your team for delegating tasks</div><div>â€¢ Engaging in follow through and reporting; closing the loop</div><div>â€¢ Showing humility</div><div>â€¢ Recognizing that everyone has something to bring to the table (we all have different&nbsp;</div><div>assets)</div><div>â€¢ Being inclusive</div><div>Data-Driven</div><div>â€¢ Evidence-based practice</div><div>â€¢ Being transparent even if it presents risk</div><div>â€¢ Having specific intent; purpose behind practice</div><div>â€¢ Recognizing that â€œgoodâ€ data is effective, powerful (tells a story), &amp; initiates change</div><div>Servant Leadership</div><div>â€¢ Basing your style of leadership on whatâ€™s good for the group</div><div>â€¢ Not caring about getting credit</div><div>â€