(18, 118, 'Type', 'Types', '&amp;lt;h2 style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; position: relative; clear: both; font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; font-size: 38px; line-height: 42px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-top: 45px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;div style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;a name=&amp;quot;types&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;What are the different types of heart failure?&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/h2&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Heart failure can occur in either the left or right side of your heart. It&rsquo;s also possible for both sides of your heart to fail at the same time.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Heart failure is also classified as either diastolic or systolic.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;h3 style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; clear: both; font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; font-size: 26px; line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 35px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Left-sided heart failure&amp;lt;/h3&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Left-sided heart failure is the most common type of heart failure.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;The&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.healthline.com/human-body-maps/left-ventricle&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;left heart ventricle&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp;is located in the bottom left side of your heart. This area pumps oxygen-rich blood to the rest of your body.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Left-sided heart failure occurs when the left ventricle doesn&rsquo;t pump efficiently. This prevents your body from getting enough oxygen-rich blood. The blood backs up into your lungs instead, which causes shortness of breath and a&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.healthline.com/health/pleural-effusion&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;buildup of fluid&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;h3 style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; clear: both; font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; font-size: 26px; line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 35px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Right-sided heart failure&amp;lt;/h3&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;The&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.healthline.com/human-body-maps/right-ventricle&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;right heart ventricle&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp;is responsible for pumping blood to your lungs to collect oxygen. Right-sided heart failure occurs when the right side of your heart can&rsquo;t perform its job effectively. It&rsquo;s usually triggered by left-sided heart failure. The accumulation of blood in the lungs caused by left-sided heart failure makes the right ventricle work harder. This can stress the right side of the heart and cause it to fail.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Right-sided heart failure can also occur as a result of other conditions, such as&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.healthline.com/health/understanding-idiopathic-pulmonary-fibrosis/chronic-lung-diseases-causes-and-risk-factors&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;lung disease&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;. According to the&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/heart-failure/symptoms-causes/syc-20373142&amp;quot; target=&amp;quot;_blank&amp;quot; rel=&amp;quot;noopener noreferrer&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Mayo Clinic&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;, right-sided heart failure is marked by&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.healthline.com/symptom/swelling&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;swelling&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp;of the lower extremities. This swelling is caused by fluid backup in the legs,&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.healthline.com/symptom/swollen-ankle&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;feet&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;, and abdomen.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;h3 style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; clear: both; font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; font-size: 26px; line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 35px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Diastolic heart failure&amp;lt;/h3&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Diastolic heart failure occurs when the heart muscle becomes stiffer than normal. The stiffness, which is usually due to&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.healthline.com/health/heart-disease&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;heart disease&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;, means that your heart doesn&rsquo;t fill with blood easily. This is known as diastolic dysfunction. It leads to a lack of blood flow to the rest of the organs in your body.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Diastolic heart failure is more common in women than in men.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;h3 style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; clear: both; font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; font-size: 26px; line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 35px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Systolic heart failure&amp;lt;/h3&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Systolic heart failure occurs when the heart muscle loses its ability to contract. The contractions of the heart are necessary to pump oxygen-rich blood out to the body. This problem is known as systolic dysfunction, and it usually develops when your heart is weak and&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.healthline.com/health/mild-cardiomegaly&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;enlarged&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Systolic heart failure is more common in men than in women.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Both diastolic and systolic heart failure can occur on the left or right sides of the heart. You may have either condition on both sides of the heart.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;', '&amp;lt;h2 style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; position: relative; clear: both; font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; font-size: 38px; line-height: 42px; margin-bottom: 15px; margin-top: 45px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;div style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;a name=&amp;quot;types&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;What are the different types of heart failure?&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/h2&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Heart failure can occur in either the left or right side of your heart. It&rsquo;s also possible for both sides of your heart to fail at the same time.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Heart failure is also classified as either diastolic or systolic.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;h3 style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; clear: both; font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; font-size: 26px; line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 35px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Left-sided heart failure&amp;lt;/h3&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Left-sided heart failure is the most common type of heart failure.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;The&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.healthline.com/human-body-maps/left-ventricle&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;left heart ventricle&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp;is located in the bottom left side of your heart. This area pumps oxygen-rich blood to the rest of your body.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Left-sided heart failure occurs when the left ventricle doesn&rsquo;t pump efficiently. This prevents your body from getting enough oxygen-rich blood. The blood backs up into your lungs instead, which causes shortness of breath and a&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.healthline.com/health/pleural-effusion&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;buildup of fluid&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;h3 style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; clear: both; font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; font-size: 26px; line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 35px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Right-sided heart failure&amp;lt;/h3&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;The&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.healthline.com/human-body-maps/right-ventricle&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;right heart ventricle&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp;is responsible for pumping blood to your lungs to collect oxygen. Right-sided heart failure occurs when the right side of your heart can&rsquo;t perform its job effectively. It&rsquo;s usually triggered by left-sided heart failure. The accumulation of blood in the lungs caused by left-sided heart failure makes the right ventricle work harder. This can stress the right side of the heart and cause it to fail.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Right-sided heart failure can also occur as a result of other conditions, such as&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.healthline.com/health/understanding-idiopathic-pulmonary-fibrosis/chronic-lung-diseases-causes-and-risk-factors&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;lung disease&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;. According to the&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/heart-failure/symptoms-causes/syc-20373142&amp;quot; target=&amp;quot;_blank&amp;quot; rel=&amp;quot;noopener noreferrer&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Mayo Clinic&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;, right-sided heart failure is marked by&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.healthline.com/symptom/swelling&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;swelling&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;&amp;amp;nbsp;of the lower extremities. This swelling is caused by fluid backup in the legs,&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.healthline.com/symptom/swollen-ankle&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;feet&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;, and abdomen.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;h3 style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; clear: both; font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; font-size: 26px; line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 35px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Diastolic heart failure&amp;lt;/h3&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Diastolic heart failure occurs when the heart muscle becomes stiffer than normal. The stiffness, which is usually due to&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.healthline.com/health/heart-disease&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;heart disease&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;, means that your heart doesn&rsquo;t fill with blood easily. This is known as diastolic dysfunction. It leads to a lack of blood flow to the rest of the organs in your body.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Diastolic heart failure is more common in women than in men.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;h3 style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; clear: both; font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; font-size: 26px; line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-top: 35px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Systolic heart failure&amp;lt;/h3&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Systolic heart failure occurs when the heart muscle loses its ability to contract. The contractions of the heart are necessary to pump oxygen-rich blood out to the body. This problem is known as systolic dysfunction, and it usually develops when your heart is weak and&amp;amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;a href=&amp;quot;https://www.healthline.com/health/mild-cardiomegaly&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;content-link css-5r4717&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; border-color: currentcolor; color: rgb(1, 173, 185);&amp;quot;&amp;gt;enlarged&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Systolic heart failure is more common in men than in women.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;lt;p style=&amp;quot;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; box-sizing: inherit; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 18px; line-height: 26px; color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-family: &amp;amp;quot;Proxima Nova&amp;amp;quot;, system-ui, sans-serif;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;Both diastolic and systolic heart failure can occur on the left or right sides of the heart. You may have either condition on both sides of the heart.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;'),
